<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Cops spokesman Lt Col Thulani Zwane said his premises was searched and an unlicensed firearm and ammunition were recovered as well as a cellphone.The suspects will appear in the Richards Bay Magistrates’ Court to face business robbery and kidnapping charges and a further possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition for third suspect on Friday."On 12 December at 17.40, the victim was at his business premises in Richards Bay when the suspects approached him. The suspects allegedly pointed him with a firearm and took an undisclosed amount of cash. "They allegedly kidnapped his friend and drove away in their VW Polo getaway vehicle. Later, the kidnapped victim was released. A case of business robbery and kidnapping was opened at Richards Bay police station."The KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa praised the members for arresting the suspects.